<br>
also you arent using /pet die are you? I didnt think that was an actual pet death cmd - use /pet get lost<br>
<br>
Also doesnt the PoP ui have a pet command box with pet atk, guard, back off, and get lost? has a green pet hp bar too.  Mine does (may have been from some alternate ui) and I can simply click a pet get lost button on it - no typing needed (since a typo could = death :P ).<br>
<br>
I wait till pet is low on health (- how much is determined by how fast pet is losing health, what mob hits for, etc) then begin casting new pet, when spell is very close to finishing I will click my pet kill button, and my new pet is ready almost right away. I then send it in after mob which is rumbling right towards me. <br>
<br>
I find it better to not build up aggro on mobs I have to chain fight, as when your next pet is ready, it has no aggro built up and you may find yourself getting beaten up for a bit until the new pet can get the mobs attention. What i mean by this is if you know you have to chain pets to kill something, dont go overboard nuking while the first few pets are up, if you have to nuke alot maybe wait till the last few pets. Every situation is different though.<br>
<br>
Limpy<br>
